text_blocks.snippet: As of February 2026, Ed Sheeran is 34 years old. He is a highly proficient multi-instrumentalist and songwriter who primarily resides in a sprawling estate in Suffolk, England, while maintaining a significant presence in New York City.
Sheeran’s career spans several key roles within the music industry, characterized by high levels of technical and creative proficiency:

list.snippet: Singer-Songwriter: Regarded as a master songwriter, he has written for himself and major artists like One Direction and Taylor Swift. His proficiency is evidenced by multiple Ivor Novello Awards for Songwriter of the Year.
Guitar: Expert proficiency; known for a "virtuoso" style that blends percussive slapping, "chugging," and intricate fingerstyle techniques.
Vocals: High proficiency; recognized for a versatile range that spans soulful pop, folk, and rhythmic hip-hop delivery.
Live Looping: Elite proficiency; he is famous for using a custom-built looper pedal to layer vocals, percussion, and guitar live, effectively acting as a "one-man band".
Record Producer: He frequently produces or co-produces his own albums and has his own record label, Gingerbread Man Records.
Actor: Occasional roles, notably appearing in Game of Thrones, Yesterday, and The Bastard Executioner.

text_blocks.snippet: Sheeran maintains a global real estate portfolio but divides most of his time between two major locations:

list.snippet: Primary Residence: A 16-acre compound known as "Sheeranville" located just outside Framlingham, Suffolk, England.
U.S. Residence: He recently purchased a $12 million condo in the Brooklyn Heights neighborhood of Brooklyn, New York (located at the Pierhouse development), which serves as his permanent U.S. base.
